# GitHub Personal Access Token
# Required for fetching contribution data and repository information
#
# How to create:
# 1. Go to GitHub Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens → Tokens (classic)
# 2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Give it a descriptive name (e.g., "gh-magic-matrix-local")
# 4. Select minimal required scopes:
#    - For public repos: no scopes needed (uncheck all)
#    - For private repos: check "repo" scope
# 5. Click "Generate token"
# 6. Copy the token immediately (you won't see it again)
#
# Setup:
# 1. Copy this file to .env (not tracked by git)
#    cp .env.example .env
# 2. Replace the placeholder below with your actual token
# 3. Never commit your real token to git!
#
# Token rotation:
# - Rotate tokens regularly (every 90 days recommended)
# - Revoke immediately if exposed or no longer needed
# - Use fine-grained tokens with minimal permissions when possible
#
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_github_token_here_replace_this

# Alternative environment variable names (for compatibility)
# The application will check these in order:
# 1. GITHUB_TOKEN (preferred)
# 2. GH_TOKEN
# 3. GITHUB_PAT
#
# GH_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here
# GITHUB_PAT=ghp_your_token_here
